<br>
I'm hoping that line of thinking isn't terribly incorrect.  <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica" size="+1">Perilbane Mooncaster</font><br>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica" size="-1">Arch Mage of the 60th Circle<br>
Master Summoner of Essentially useless junk.</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#333333>(12/13/02 5:27:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Seeking magely advice and opinions...</span><hr size=1> Your situation pretty much sounds like mine.  I can play at odd times for 1-3 hours, with the caveat that I might need to drop out at any time.  I solo a lot, since that's something that I can do to be &quot;productive&quot;.<br>
<br>
My guild is small, and averages 10 levels under me.<br>
<br>
My plans were to do the same... level to 60, pad myself, and then solo in FG or do short-term groups in PoP for AA until I get Ward of Xegony.  At that point, it makes sense to level to 61. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 805<br> <font color=#333333>(12/25/02 5:52:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Seeking magely advice and opinions...</span><hr size=1> From my point of view, it is a good idea to get appropriate AA's to assist you with your exp endeavors.  By level 59 you should have enough AA's to get Master Title (pref Spell Casting Mastery 3), and by 60-61 you should have almost enough AA's for Sage title.<br>
<br>
AA's alone don't necessarily do enough for you, and levels alone, in my highly biased opinion, don't show enough depth and breadth for your character's abilities at any given level.<br>
<br>
Balance between levels and AA's is the best advice I can offer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khysanth>Khysanth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#333333>(12/25/02 7:43:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   For me...</span><hr size=1> I just dinged 60 not too long ago.<br>
<br>
Some days i'll go 100% into AA and some days 100% into reg. xp.<br>
<br>
I have 2 AAs as well. <br>
<br>
Once I get my first 6 AAs (the essentials, run speed and regen) i'm going full force to 65.<br>
<br>
Even at 65, in a full group in PoV/PoS you get 2% AA per kill - its insanely fast. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showPrevMessage?topicID=326.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showNextMessage?topicID=326.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.threadControl?topicID=326.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=326.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=326.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerf